The leaders of Canada, the European Commission, the European Council, France, Germany, Italy, Japan, the Netherlands, Spain, the United Kingdom, and the United States have condemned Russia's missile attacks on Ukrainian cities and civilian infrastructure. They also discussed an explosion near the border of Poland and Ukraine and offered their support for Poland's ongoing investigation. The leaders reaffirmed their support for Ukraine in the face of Russian aggression and expressed condolences to the families of the victims in Poland and Ukraine.